record_data.record_plain_text: Dairyland Power Cooperative Rate Schedule FERC No. 2 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Dairyland Power Cooperative (“Dairyland” or “DPC”) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Supply Service”) from the listed facilities located in the Dairyland pricing zone in the Midwest Independent Transmission System Operator, Inc. (“Midwest ISO”) transmission footprint. Also listed is Dairyland’s 30% ownership of the Weston 4 power plant located in the Wisconsin Public Service pricing zone. This tariff sets forth DPC’s revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Supply Service from the listed facilities pursuant to the Reactive Power Revenue Requirements in Schedule 2 of the Midwest ISO’s Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserves Markets Tariff (“ASM Tariff”). REVENUE REQUIREMENT: DPC’s revenue requirements for the specified facilities shall be calculated as follows: J. P. Madgett (JPM) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $236,592 Monthly Revenue Requirement $19,716 Genoa Station No. 3 (G3) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $370,447 Monthly Revenue Requirement $30,871 30% of Weston 4 (W4) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $251,256 Monthly Revenue Requirement $20,938 Alma Units 1-3 (ALM 1-3) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $23,475 Monthly Revenue Requirement $1,956 Elk Mound Units 1-2 (ELM 1-2) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $142,110 Monthly Revenue Requirement $11,842 Flambeau Units 1-3 (FKM 1-3) Power Plant Annual Revenue Requirement $178,252 Monthly Revenue Requirement $14,854
